sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:16:CypherClaw is an autonomous music-making entity that has been running continuously for ~12 days at the time of this PRD, composing through a SuperCollider-driven duet composer with seven voices (pluck, breath, choir, kotekan, pad, bowed, tabla_tin) across scenes whose arc phases cycle Listen / Conversation / Divination / Procession. It currently outputs through one master reverb on a JACK graph and is heard only inside the room where the box lives.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:20:1. **Per-voice reverb spaces** — each voice in its own evocative reverberant space (CypherClaw chose specific spaces per voice)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:21:2. **MIDI file ingestion** — watch folder of external MIDI gets mined for fragments and used as variation seeds; an opt-in `--faithful-transmission` mode preserves structural content
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:27:8. **Cross-voice coupling** — shared affective-state bus per voice family; voices react to each other's expression intensity
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:42:- All seven voices live: pluck, breath, choir, kotekan, pad, bowed, tabla_tin (5 quarantined voices forward to safe substitutes: gong, bell, metal, tabla_ge, grain)
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:88:1. CypherClaw sounds **deeper** — every voice lives in a believable space, every note carries performance-level expression, gestures cohere across voices as an ensemble.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:89:2. CypherClaw becomes **its own thing** musically — it composes in microtonal tunings that morph through arcs, in meters that bend mid-song, with expression that shapes notes the way a performer shapes notes.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:91:4. CypherClaw is **open to outside influence on its own terms** — MIDI dropped into a watch folder gets metabolized into vocabulary and variations, occasionally rendered faithfully when the operator flags it.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:106:- This PRD does **not** propose retuning or recomposing existing scenes. The new tuning systems and expression layer apply going forward; back-catalog scenes remain in their original form.
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:134:- The composer's mood-driven layer selects per-scene whether to use *matched* (default, per-voice space as above), *expressive* (deliberate mismatch), or *house-bound* (all voices share the active house patch's space).
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:140:- New: `my-claw/tools/senseweave/synthesis/spaces/` directory with one `.scd` per space, and (if convolution path) an `irs/` subdirectory with `.wav` impulse responses
sdp/prd-cypherclaw-v2-2026-05-22.md:144:**Default decision:** Engineering decision — start with Path A (algorithmic). If listening sessions reveal the spaces don't read as the described environments, escalate Path B.
